1
00:00:23,876 --> 00:00:25,459
Seol Nae Il.

2
00:00:25,459 --> 00:00:26,568
Why are you here?

3
00:00:28,111 --> 00:00:29,663
Isn't it your turn soon?

4
00:01:02,882 --> 00:01:03,952
Okay.

5
00:01:04,982 --> 00:01:06,567
Let's stop.

6
00:01:08,844 --> 00:01:11,230
It's disappointing after coming this far,

7
00:01:12,787 --> 00:01:14,680
but if you don't want to,

8
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:17,369
let's stop.

9
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:30,516
Let's go home.

10
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:52,626
Cha Yoo Jin will go beyond you.

11
00:01:52,626 --> 00:01:55,431
He will fly far away.

12
00:01:57,617 --> 00:02:01,167
Baby, if you want to stay with Yoo Jin,

13
00:02:01,167 --> 00:02:05,475
you have to face music head-on.

14
00:02:17,012 --> 00:02:20,959
Sunbae, I'm going in.

15
00:02:20,959 --> 00:02:22,951
I should perform.

16
00:02:27,417 --> 00:02:29,209
It's okay.

17
00:02:29,209 --> 00:02:30,928
You don't need to push yourself.

18
00:02:31,902 --> 00:02:34,069
No one will say anything to you.

19
00:02:34,709 --> 00:02:36,299
No.

20
00:02:37,542 --> 00:02:39,395
I want to do it.

21
00:02:40,185 --> 00:02:42,237
I can play the music.

22
00:02:54,257 --> 00:02:57,292
Yes, please notify the judges.

23
00:02:57,292 --> 00:02:59,791
I will bring the next contestant soon.

24
00:03:00,889 --> 00:03:02,042
Wait!

25
00:03:02,042 --> 00:03:05,542
No. 7! No. 7 hasn't given up yet!

26
00:03:05,542 --> 00:03:07,557
Contestant No. 7 just came back.

27
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:10,500
Then what should I do...

28
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:14,105
I will do my best! Please let me play!

29
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:25,209
It's already been reported,
so we have to get an approval.

30
00:03:25,209 --> 00:03:26,480
No.

31
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:29,369
No.

32
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:49,334
What's taking Nae Il so long?

33
00:03:49,334 --> 00:03:51,866
I hope nothing went wrong.

34
00:04:02,201 --> 00:04:05,004
Did Nae Il run away?

35
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:08,559
No way, she came all the way here.

36
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:11,168
I don't think she did.

37
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:13,975
Seol Nae Il, you haven't changed.

38
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:18,667
Pour in your anger and emotional garbage
into your performance.

39
00:05:18,667 --> 00:05:23,959
That will help create your own performance.

40
00:05:23,959 --> 00:05:27,590
Throw everything in the performance.

41
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:29,702
After that...

42
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:35,252
you can go back to your happy self as usual.

43
00:05:37,296 --> 00:05:42,083
You have nothing to be afraid of
in front of the piano, Baby!

44
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:11,997
I didn't know
there was this version of La Campanella.

45
00:06:12,709 --> 00:06:14,697
It's really nice.

46
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:32,125
It's a performance fitting of Seol Nae Il.

47
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,464
A piano performance
like the one by an orchestra.

48
00:06:34,464 --> 00:06:37,767
And that's your performance.

49
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:54,706
It's been a long time, Seol Nae Il.

50
00:06:54,709 --> 00:06:56,716
Are you in a music college?

51
00:07:05,384 --> 00:07:07,751
Seol Nae Il, didn't you practice?

52
00:07:07,751 --> 00:07:09,772
Do you want to stay up all night?

53
00:08:16,292 --> 00:08:20,584
Scores for Contestant No. 7 vary too much.

54
00:08:20,584 --> 00:08:22,500
Obviously.

55
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:26,500
Her performance was too unconventional.

56
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:30,459
That's right.
This is a competition, not her recital.

57
00:08:30,459 --> 00:08:34,083
We should never forget our rules
in this competition.

58
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:37,375
I like her performance,
but I am worried to be honest.

59
00:08:37,375 --> 00:08:40,292
If you award her,
other students will mimic her.

60
00:08:40,292 --> 00:08:43,751
They think it's okay
to ignore the notes and the scores.

61
00:08:43,751 --> 00:08:46,292
What are you so afraid of?

62
00:08:46,292 --> 00:08:50,459
It's easy to pick out
bad and wrong performances.

63
00:08:50,459 --> 00:08:54,209
But for good, well-played performances...

64
00:08:54,209 --> 00:08:58,834
especially for unique performances,

65
00:08:58,834 --> 00:09:01,041
it's very difficult to judge them.

66
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:04,375
But isn't that our job?

67
00:09:04,375 --> 00:09:08,083
But she also hesitated and made mistakes.

68
00:09:08,083 --> 00:09:11,391
We should never look over them
in the competition.

69
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:18,928
Then let's do this.

70
00:09:23,834 --> 00:09:26,292
Wow, your performance was really great.

71
00:09:26,292 --> 00:09:28,763
I've never heard La Campanella like that.

72
00:09:32,125 --> 00:09:35,292
Do you have the score for that variation?

73
00:09:35,292 --> 00:09:37,419
The score...

74
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:40,873
Score?

75
00:09:40,876 --> 00:09:43,978
Excuse me, did I play differently
from the score?

76
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:50,375
We will announce the winners now.

77
00:09:50,375 --> 00:09:51,846
They're making an announcement.

78
00:10:03,209 --> 00:10:07,125
It's the first time
I'm getting nervous at a competition.

79
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:08,584
Me too.

80
00:10:08,584 --> 00:10:11,887
My students never made it to a competition.

81
00:10:20,829 --> 00:10:23,048
Let's talk again later.

82
00:10:24,943 --> 00:10:30,083
You didn't bring her to the music festival
for no reason, Maestro.

83
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:35,828
I do have a knack for recognizing talent.

84
00:10:37,089 --> 00:10:40,083
Talent alone is not enough.

85
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:45,880
Without true passion,
students will face their limit in the end.

86
00:10:46,522 --> 00:10:51,910
But luckily, that student seems
to have found passion now.

87
00:10:54,154 --> 00:10:57,684
I guess I'm old now.

88
00:10:59,117 --> 00:11:04,959
I like watching students grow
more than my own performances.

89
00:11:04,959 --> 00:11:06,641
Really?

90
00:11:09,655 --> 00:11:13,000
Please come to the stage
when we call your name.

91
00:11:14,792 --> 00:11:16,474
Third place.

92
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:20,014
No. 3, Mr. Yoo Sung Min.

93
00:11:32,042 --> 00:11:33,885
Up next, second place.

94
00:11:36,154 --> 00:11:38,498
The second place goes to...

95
00:11:40,087 --> 00:11:45,476
contestant No. 6, Miss Kim Ga Ram.

96
00:11:54,047 --> 00:11:58,209
If Kim Ga Ram is second place,
our Nae Il must be first place!

97
00:11:58,209 --> 00:12:01,054
Of course! Nae Il is the only one!

98
00:12:06,626 --> 00:12:07,803
Lastly,

99
00:12:08,459 --> 00:12:11,806
the winner of Baek Geon Soo Piano Competition
this year is...

100
00:12:24,686 --> 00:12:26,655
We don't have one.

101
00:12:28,439 --> 00:12:33,626
The second place is the final winner
without a first place this year.

102
00:12:33,626 --> 00:12:36,414
Thank you, everyone.

103
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:50,542
In the Baek Geon Soo Competition,

104
00:12:50,542 --> 00:12:53,584
the winner's seat has never been left empty.

105
00:12:53,584 --> 00:12:56,542
Why is my Ga Ram the second place
when there is no winner?

106
00:12:56,542 --> 00:12:58,125
Why didn't they give her the first place?

107
00:12:58,125 --> 00:13:01,459
Someone else deserved to be first place.

108
00:13:01,459 --> 00:13:03,292
Wouldn't that be the case?

109
00:13:03,292 --> 00:13:05,110
Of course.

110
00:13:27,173 --> 00:13:31,727
Thank you, Boss. Thanks, Mini Min Hee.

111
00:13:33,689 --> 00:13:35,616
Sunbae.

112
00:13:38,918 --> 00:13:42,680
Is there a place that Nae Il would go,
in this building?

113
00:13:44,122 --> 00:13:46,049
I'll look for her.

114
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,235
Hello?

115
00:14:13,863 --> 00:14:16,748
Yes, Mom.

116
00:14:20,626 --> 00:14:24,292
I really did my best.

117
00:14:24,292 --> 00:14:26,015
Mom.

118
00:14:26,825 --> 00:14:31,838
What do I do when things don't work out,
no matter how hard I try?

119
00:14:48,513 --> 00:14:52,000
Sunbae, it's cold outside.
Why are you standing here?

120
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,639
It's cold out, so where have you been?

121
00:14:57,272 --> 00:14:58,949
Dinner?

122
00:15:00,178 --> 00:15:02,105
Did you eat?

123
00:15:14,042 --> 00:15:15,834
It's tuna kimchi stew.

124
00:15:15,834 --> 00:15:18,261
Since it's cold, have the broth first.

125
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:42,564
I liked that

126
00:15:43,667 --> 00:15:46,663
at least you didn't run away.

127
00:15:47,995 --> 00:15:50,626
You performed better than anyone else.

128
00:15:50,626 --> 00:15:53,667
There are lots of competitions.

129
00:15:53,667 --> 00:15:55,798
You can try out for another one.

130
00:15:57,749 --> 00:16:03,472
Still, there are no competitions
that offer study abroad.

131
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:08,184
Good.

132
00:16:08,932 --> 00:16:10,920
You don't get to go.

133
00:16:11,904 --> 00:16:13,584
And I don't get to go either.

134
00:16:35,417 --> 00:16:37,709
[Hypnosis Lessons]

135
00:17:00,646 --> 00:17:02,697
Are you studying hypnosis?

136
00:17:05,385 --> 00:17:06,250
Why are you hiding it?

137
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:10,206
It's nothing.
I was just startled because of you.

138
00:17:19,207 --> 00:17:20,967
Are you interested in hypnosis?

139
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:23,834
No, I'm just bored.

140
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:26,542
So you get bored even when you have someone.

141
00:17:26,542 --> 00:17:27,880
You should ask him to hang out with you.

142
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:30,542
Yoo Jin Sunbae is busy right now.

143
00:17:30,542 --> 00:17:32,687
Great. I'm free.

144
00:17:33,929 --> 00:17:37,066
Sunbae, you're not allowed to come on to me.

145
00:17:38,244 --> 00:17:40,292
Nae Il, you have principles.

146
00:17:40,292 --> 00:17:42,947
I like women with principles.

147
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:52,581
It must be tough for you
because of the competition.

148
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:56,077
I forgot about it.

149
00:17:56,077 --> 00:17:58,838
There will be other competitions.

150
00:18:00,498 --> 00:18:03,042
Yeah, you can win next year.

151
00:18:03,042 --> 00:18:06,345
But I won't ever be first place.

152
00:18:06,970 --> 00:18:10,523
I practiced so much,
but I still didn't make it.

153
00:18:12,044 --> 00:18:14,083
I guess my piano performance

154
00:18:14,083 --> 00:18:17,542
is not something
that can be recognized in competitions.

155
00:18:17,542 --> 00:18:18,983
Nae Il.

156
00:18:20,264 --> 00:18:22,751
Anyway, you're not allowed to come on to me!

157
00:18:22,751 --> 00:18:25,323
You can't come near me.

158
00:18:25,957 --> 00:18:28,500
I won't come on to you.

159
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:31,529
So why don't you just lean on me?

160
00:18:31,529 --> 00:18:35,541
I know how upset you must be right now.

161
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:42,039
Sunbae, I'm fine.

162
00:18:42,042 --> 00:18:44,425
I can go for another one next year.

163
00:18:53,134 --> 00:18:56,312
Franz! It's been a while.

164
00:18:57,136 --> 00:19:00,092
Mom, we're in the middle
of an important conversation.

165
00:19:00,751 --> 00:19:03,736
I made you your favorite black tea coffee.

166
00:19:04,812 --> 00:19:07,405
It's a new item. Please enjoy.

167
00:19:11,985 --> 00:19:13,245
It smells nice.

168
00:19:14,812 --> 00:19:18,993
I'm working on your study abroad.

169
00:19:18,993 --> 00:19:19,792
Professor.

170
00:19:19,792 --> 00:19:23,709
I told you before. I can't wait any longer.

171
00:19:23,709 --> 00:19:24,751
I already told you

172
00:19:24,751 --> 00:19:27,125
that I have no thoughts
of studying abroad yet.

173
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:29,667
It's disappointing that you can't go together

174
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:33,083
but Baby can come next year.

175
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:37,459
Once the college orchestra festival is over,

176
00:19:37,459 --> 00:19:39,417
leave the country.

177
00:19:39,417 --> 00:19:42,942
This is an order as your professor.

178
00:19:45,575 --> 00:19:47,542
Cha Yoo Jin is going to study abroad?

179
00:19:47,542 --> 00:19:48,959
I haven't heard that.

180
00:19:48,959 --> 00:19:50,959
My professor told me

181
00:19:50,959 --> 00:19:52,876
that Professor von Stresemann is working
on it.

182
00:19:52,876 --> 00:19:56,375
Isn't it obvious
that Yoo Jin would go study abroad?

183
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:58,792
It's natural for him.

184
00:19:58,792 --> 00:20:02,292
Then who will conduct Rising Star?

185
00:20:02,292 --> 00:20:04,213
Right?

186
00:20:09,256 --> 00:20:11,168
What about Rising Star?

187
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:13,005
It just settled.

188
00:20:13,005 --> 00:20:14,549
How could they manage without a conductor?

189
00:20:14,549 --> 00:20:17,309
Are you the only conductor in the world?

190
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:24,334
Like you said, you've found your place.

191
00:20:24,334 --> 00:20:26,527
Why are you trying
to take responsibility for it?

192
00:20:27,270 --> 00:20:29,417
There are a lot of conductors other than you.

193
00:20:29,417 --> 00:20:32,626
Why don't we call
the assistant conductor tomorrow?

194
00:20:32,626 --> 00:20:33,626
Assistant conductor?

195
00:20:33,626 --> 00:20:36,167
He's not bad.

196
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:38,375
Take him in and teach him.

197
00:20:38,375 --> 00:20:40,499
Who are you talking about?

198
00:20:42,288 --> 00:20:45,580
Nice to meet you. My name is Lee Yoon Hoo.

199
00:20:45,580 --> 00:20:48,666
I see that I've met some of you before.

200
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:50,209
It's my Yoon Hoo.

201
00:20:50,209 --> 00:20:52,636
Hi, Yoon Hoo.

202
00:20:58,176 --> 00:20:59,810
You're here!

203
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:07,459
I just talked to the members.

204
00:21:07,459 --> 00:21:09,209
You don't need to introduce me.

205
00:21:09,209 --> 00:21:10,751
You're the assistant conductor?

206
00:21:10,751 --> 00:21:13,065
Yeah, aren't you glad to see me?

207
00:21:13,065 --> 00:21:16,744
Not sure. We don't get along too well.

208
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:22,834
I told you to fix your way of speech.
You're very consistent.

209
00:21:22,834 --> 00:21:24,577
I wish you'd be glad to see me.

210
00:21:24,577 --> 00:21:26,629
Don't hurt my feelings.

211
00:21:32,168 --> 00:21:34,678
When are you transferring
to the conducting major?

212
00:21:35,382 --> 00:21:37,626
I'll go through
the transfer process next year.

213
00:21:37,626 --> 00:21:40,500
I came with a recommendation
from Professor von Stresemann.

214
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:41,644
I guess you didn't know.

215
00:21:47,391 --> 00:21:49,443
I'm going to begin our practice.

216
00:21:54,606 --> 00:21:55,991
Let's get ready.

217
00:23:03,576 --> 00:23:06,097
You're entering
the college orchestra festival, right?

218
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:09,042
I heard you're going against Sae Hyun?

219
00:23:09,042 --> 00:23:11,557
I heard they're incredible.

220
00:23:11,557 --> 00:23:14,167
Are you okay at this level?

221
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:15,876
Just worry about yourself first.

222
00:23:15,876 --> 00:23:18,262
I accepted you because of our Professor.

223
00:23:18,889 --> 00:23:21,536
But you're not qualified
to be assistant conductor now.

224
00:23:23,097 --> 00:23:25,375
You're worried about me?

225
00:23:25,375 --> 00:23:30,876
I heard Stresemann conducted
with his left hand in his pocket.

226
00:23:30,876 --> 00:23:34,083
And I'm getting physical therapy.

227
00:23:34,083 --> 00:23:37,489
If you really want to learn,
practice using your left hand first.

228
00:23:37,489 --> 00:23:39,626
There is no time to worry about me.

229
00:23:39,626 --> 00:23:41,418
What are you going to do?

230
00:23:43,861 --> 00:23:46,288
The team is completely divided.

231
00:23:49,764 --> 00:23:50,912
I see.

232
00:23:51,751 --> 00:23:54,401
That's why they came to see me.

233
00:23:57,771 --> 00:24:00,198
They were worried
about what will happen after you leave.

234
00:24:05,778 --> 00:24:09,250
So, you might not know this but...

235
00:24:09,250 --> 00:24:12,482
They look down on us all the time,
calling us the losers.

236
00:24:12,482 --> 00:24:15,167
Yes, they do that even now.

237
00:24:15,167 --> 00:24:17,539
Once Cha Yoo Jin leaves to go study abroad,

238
00:24:17,539 --> 00:24:20,042
they will kick all of us out.

239
00:24:20,042 --> 00:24:24,669
My friend, you have to join us
so that we can look forward to the future.

240
00:24:27,675 --> 00:24:29,250
Where are you going?

241
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:32,292
They looked like
they'd have a brawl after we left.

242
00:24:32,292 --> 00:24:35,125
Are they kids?
I'm sure they'll take care of it.

243
00:24:35,125 --> 00:24:36,250
I guess.

244
00:24:36,250 --> 00:24:39,918
In that environment,
Rising Star will break up soon.

245
00:24:39,918 --> 00:24:41,895
Even if you don't do anything.

246
00:24:44,388 --> 00:24:47,650
Didn't you come as the assistant conductor
to learn how to conduct?

247
00:24:52,167 --> 00:24:54,417
You told me before.

248
00:24:54,417 --> 00:24:56,284
That it's obvious I haven't had many friends.

249
00:24:57,754 --> 00:24:58,774
Then,

250
00:24:59,626 --> 00:25:01,934
why didn't I have friends?

251
00:25:03,075 --> 00:25:06,721
Because you only had rivals
who were disguised as friends.

252
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:11,792
That's why I'm used to this.

253
00:25:11,792 --> 00:25:14,334
Fighting, jealousy, war.

254
00:25:14,334 --> 00:25:17,209
It's not a feeling that's been built overnight.

255
00:25:17,209 --> 00:25:18,667
The ones who used to be enemies
before Rising Star

256
00:25:18,667 --> 00:25:20,966
are gathered together.

257
00:25:20,966 --> 00:25:23,083
It would be strange
if it worked out right away.

258
00:25:23,083 --> 00:25:24,250
It's a necessary process.

259
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:27,856
Pain bursts in that process.

260
00:25:28,993 --> 00:25:30,792
It's a little unexpected.

261
00:25:30,792 --> 00:25:33,653
I didn't know Cha Yoo Jin was so incapable.

262
00:25:34,575 --> 00:25:39,709
Did you join the orchestra
to see when it bursts?

263
00:25:39,709 --> 00:25:42,029
I don't like Rising Star right now.

264
00:25:42,029 --> 00:25:43,292
I'm just going to take care of my friends.

265
00:25:43,292 --> 00:25:45,584
Is this some kid's joke?

266
00:25:45,584 --> 00:25:47,417
I'm not joking either.

267
00:25:49,883 --> 00:25:53,312
I told you to stay on your toes.

268
00:25:55,342 --> 00:25:57,125
Why don't you watch out?

269
00:25:57,125 --> 00:25:58,603
It pisses me off.

270
00:26:01,006 --> 00:26:02,724
Watch your back.

271
00:26:13,417 --> 00:26:16,918
[Hypnotherapy Specialist
Kim Jae Won]

272
00:26:19,189 --> 00:26:24,542
To create a key, you should know
how the lock is structured first.

273
00:26:24,542 --> 00:26:27,375
The most important thing in hypnotherapy is

274
00:26:27,375 --> 00:26:30,971
to identify the real existence of the trauma.

275
00:26:55,737 --> 00:26:58,417
You keep holding that these days.

276
00:26:58,417 --> 00:27:00,709
You don't need that to tell time.

277
00:27:03,070 --> 00:27:04,167
What?

278
00:27:04,167 --> 00:27:08,508
Sunbae, have a seat here.

279
00:27:09,254 --> 00:27:11,163
Annoying.

280
00:27:11,843 --> 00:27:13,520
What is it about?

281
00:27:36,570 --> 00:27:38,580
Yoo Jin is here.

282
00:27:40,209 --> 00:27:42,667
Yoo Jin, I heard
Nae Il did great at the competition.

283
00:27:42,667 --> 00:27:44,797
Why don't we play a piano concerto
next time?

284
00:27:44,797 --> 00:27:47,292
"Pianist Seol Nae Il following Son Soo Ji."

285
00:27:47,292 --> 00:27:48,667
She can't.

286
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:51,687
My Nae Il has to prepare
for a competition next year.

287
00:27:57,417 --> 00:27:58,667
"My Nae Il"?

288
00:27:58,667 --> 00:28:00,876
Sorry, I just blurted it out.

289
00:28:00,876 --> 00:28:02,322
Forget it.

290
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:07,500
Hearing "my Nae Il" from someone else
makes me really cringe.

291
00:28:07,500 --> 00:28:09,071
I won't say "my Nae Il" anymore.

292
00:28:09,071 --> 00:28:12,082
Why do you call my Nae Il "my Nae Il"?

293
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:15,751
Shut that mouth!

294
00:28:15,751 --> 00:28:17,375
Please stop.

295
00:28:17,375 --> 00:28:21,459
Even for Almighty Cha, this is too much.

296
00:28:21,459 --> 00:28:23,503
I have a class. See you later.

297
00:28:24,495 --> 00:28:26,334
She totally has him.

298
00:28:26,334 --> 00:28:28,290
She totally does.

299
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:30,192
Almighty Cha, you're so disappointing!

300
00:28:31,211 --> 00:28:35,990
When I said "my Nae Il",
did it make you cringe too?

301
00:28:37,050 --> 00:28:38,476
Not me, right?

302
00:28:46,226 --> 00:28:48,861
Am I crazy? Why did I do that?

303
00:28:50,143 --> 00:28:53,571
Yes, I think my Nae Il asked me.

304
00:28:55,319 --> 00:28:57,538
But even if my Nae Il asked me to...

305
00:29:09,965 --> 00:29:13,500
Really? Yoo Jin really said, "my Nae Il"?

306
00:29:13,500 --> 00:29:17,356
Yes, it was a complete shock and horror to us.

307
00:29:18,048 --> 00:29:21,417
Seol Nae Il, how did you train Yoo Jin?

308
00:29:21,417 --> 00:29:23,334
Why don't you spill the beans?

309
00:29:23,334 --> 00:29:26,876
Mini Min Hee, maybe he just happened
to say it?

310
00:29:26,876 --> 00:29:29,834
No! He said it several times.

311
00:29:29,834 --> 00:29:34,164
He was determined to say it
so that Yoon Hoo can hear it.

312
00:29:45,285 --> 00:29:51,975
When I count to the last number,
you will enter a deep relaxation state.

313
00:29:52,883 --> 00:29:58,000
Ten, nine, eight...

314
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:02,067
Deep, deeper.

315
00:30:11,351 --> 00:30:15,792
Sunbae, when you wake up from hypnosis,

316
00:30:15,792 --> 00:30:20,710
please say "my Nae Il" just ten times
in front of people.

317
00:30:34,793 --> 00:30:37,679
Sunbae, where are you now?

318
00:30:46,053 --> 00:30:48,792
I know what you heard before you came here,
so don't get ahead of yourself.

319
00:30:48,792 --> 00:30:50,334
It just blurted out of my mouth.

320
00:30:50,334 --> 00:30:52,242
How would I say "my Nae..."

321
00:30:55,203 --> 00:30:58,231
Yes, the problem is the heart.

322
00:30:58,231 --> 00:31:01,167
I'll erase these hearts first,
and change it to Seol Nae Il.

323
00:31:01,167 --> 00:31:05,464
Sunbae, you're fine now.
You can go study abroad.

324
00:31:06,281 --> 00:31:07,042
What?

325
00:31:07,042 --> 00:31:10,177
I wondered but it really worked.

326
00:31:11,661 --> 00:31:13,334
How is that possible?

327
00:31:13,334 --> 00:31:14,805
What do you mean?

328
00:31:15,853 --> 00:31:19,698
We can cure your fear of flying now.

329
00:31:21,160 --> 00:31:24,083
Sunbae, actually I...

330
00:31:24,083 --> 00:31:26,276
- Almighty Cha!
- Yoo Jin!

331
00:31:27,552 --> 00:31:30,876
Yoo Jin, is it true
that you're going abroad next month?

332
00:31:30,876 --> 00:31:33,918
It's right after our performance next month.

333
00:31:33,918 --> 00:31:34,584
I'm not going.

334
00:31:34,584 --> 00:31:37,667
I heard Professor von Stresemann is
taking you, Almighty Cha.

335
00:31:37,667 --> 00:31:39,907
He's already taking the steps in Germany.

336
00:31:39,907 --> 00:31:41,742
He decided that by himself.

337
00:31:41,742 --> 00:31:45,167
Of course we want to be with you forever.

338
00:31:45,167 --> 00:31:49,959
But our Almighty Cha can conduct
the Vienna Philharmonic.

339
00:31:49,959 --> 00:31:51,167
So you should go.

340
00:31:51,167 --> 00:31:53,094
I said I'm not going study abroad!

341
00:32:29,406 --> 00:32:33,083
This hypnosis. Even doctors couldn't do it.

342
00:32:33,083 --> 00:32:35,720
So there is no way that I would succeed.

343
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:01,626
It's a coincidence.

344
00:33:01,626 --> 00:33:04,209
If he can't cure his fear of flying,

345
00:33:04,209 --> 00:33:07,586
he won't be able to go abroad next month.

346
00:33:12,199 --> 00:33:14,203
He shouldn't go.

347
00:33:15,370 --> 00:33:18,174
I might not be able to see him again.

348
00:33:18,955 --> 00:33:21,417
Even if he leaves, he can go later.

349
00:33:21,417 --> 00:33:25,312
When I can also study abroad then.

350
00:33:34,763 --> 00:33:36,542
So, he's really leaving?

351
00:33:36,542 --> 00:33:38,876
Right? I guess Yoo Jin will leave?

352
00:33:38,876 --> 00:33:40,584
Why wouldn't he go?

353
00:33:40,584 --> 00:33:43,382
Once Almighty Cha and Shi Won leaves...

354
00:33:44,042 --> 00:33:45,667
Should I go with them?

355
00:33:45,667 --> 00:33:47,667
Shi Won? Jung Shi Won?

356
00:33:47,667 --> 00:33:49,388
Of course she would go.

357
00:33:49,388 --> 00:33:51,000
Su Min always said

358
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,459
that Shi Won is guaranteed
to study abroad in Vienna.

359
00:33:53,459 --> 00:33:55,918
But she won't leave right away.

360
00:33:55,918 --> 00:33:57,125
Of course she would.

361
00:33:57,125 --> 00:33:59,406
She said she'd leave after our performance.

362
00:34:00,691 --> 00:34:02,918
She'll leave without playing as a soloist.

363
00:34:02,918 --> 00:34:05,959
Was I stubborn for nothing?
I should've voted for Shi Won.

364
00:34:05,959 --> 00:34:08,415
It's no use to say that now.

365
00:34:18,584 --> 00:34:23,459
Yeah, I have to go to Vienna
after our concert.

366
00:34:23,459 --> 00:34:24,765
Vienna?

367
00:34:25,682 --> 00:34:28,626
Wow, I'll never be able to get there.

368
00:34:28,626 --> 00:34:30,944
How can you say that?

369
00:34:30,944 --> 00:34:33,125
- You can go.
- You and I...

370
00:34:35,017 --> 00:34:36,819
We won't be able to see each other again.

371
00:34:39,496 --> 00:34:43,550
I guess we were not that special anyway.

372
00:34:44,459 --> 00:34:46,719
We weren't that special?

373
00:34:47,905 --> 00:34:49,751
We weren't?

374
00:34:49,751 --> 00:34:54,375
Well, that's the truth.

375
00:34:54,375 --> 00:34:57,506
We didn't even get rings as a couple.

376
00:35:02,060 --> 00:35:03,569
Shi Won.

377
00:35:10,777 --> 00:35:12,453
Shi Won!

378
00:35:13,514 --> 00:35:15,751
Why does she keep coming
even when I'm mean to her?

379
00:35:15,751 --> 00:35:18,652
I don't want to see her!

380
00:35:19,993 --> 00:35:21,959
Please don't be that way, Father.

381
00:35:21,959 --> 00:35:25,250
She always looks like a boy,
so I don't like her.

382
00:35:25,250 --> 00:35:27,361
That's how she snatched
someone else's bandmaster title.

383
00:35:27,361 --> 00:35:29,663
Stop, father.

384
00:35:32,667 --> 00:35:34,542
She didn't snatch it from me.

385
00:35:34,542 --> 00:35:36,918
It was Shi Won's title to begin with.

386
00:35:36,918 --> 00:35:40,548
Shi Won should have been the soloist
to begin with.

387
00:35:40,548 --> 00:35:42,475
But I became the soloist.

388
00:35:43,156 --> 00:35:47,209
Do you like her by any chance?

389
00:35:51,777 --> 00:35:53,912
Then you should've said...

390
00:35:59,783 --> 00:36:04,500
She has really nice hair like your mother.

391
00:36:04,500 --> 00:36:06,165
Father.

392
00:36:11,380 --> 00:36:12,889
Father.

393
00:36:14,925 --> 00:36:17,394
Can I go against you just once?

394
00:37:02,345 --> 00:37:04,626
Sae Hyun is really good.

395
00:37:04,626 --> 00:37:09,395
Wow, I heard the rumors,
but I didn't know they were this good.

396
00:37:10,544 --> 00:37:14,806
Will we just get humiliated
at the college orchestra festival?

397
00:37:22,451 --> 00:37:23,835
Good.

398
00:37:25,056 --> 00:37:28,234
By the way, who brought this clip?

399
00:37:29,185 --> 00:37:33,334
I was the first one to come,
but it was already on.

400
00:37:33,334 --> 00:37:35,963
So I thought the conductor brought it.

401
00:37:40,594 --> 00:37:43,230
- Who was it?
- Who was it really?

402
00:37:44,056 --> 00:37:46,066
Why did he have this on?

403
00:37:46,683 --> 00:37:49,819
They're going to compare us with them.

404
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:55,500
Sunbae, it's strange.

405
00:37:55,500 --> 00:37:59,292
What happened today is same as before.

406
00:37:59,292 --> 00:38:01,154
The day we had a performance with A?

407
00:38:01,154 --> 00:38:02,042
You're right!

408
00:38:02,042 --> 00:38:05,256
We also heard A's performance
from the practice room.

409
00:38:05,256 --> 00:38:07,474
To discourage us!

410
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:12,002
It's a bad sign.

411
00:38:12,002 --> 00:38:14,254
We won't have
any more bad things happening, right?

412
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,727
I hope not.

413
00:38:46,366 --> 00:38:48,535
Lak Sunbae!

414
00:38:48,535 --> 00:38:50,841
Did you hurt your arm? What happened?

415
00:38:52,247 --> 00:38:55,667
It's nothing. I fell in front of my house.

416
00:38:55,667 --> 00:38:58,167
Really? Are you okay?

417
00:38:58,167 --> 00:39:00,459
Then what about the performance?

418
00:39:00,459 --> 00:39:01,626
I sprained it a little,

419
00:39:01,626 --> 00:39:04,117
so I won't have a problem playing the violin
once it's healed.

420
00:39:05,888 --> 00:39:10,525
But we'll have to choose a new soloist.

421
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:15,542
Let's give it to Shi Won.

422
00:39:15,542 --> 00:39:18,639
It's difficult to change the music anyway.

423
00:39:23,864 --> 00:39:26,249
Let's think about it until tomorrow.

424
00:39:29,828 --> 00:39:32,047
It's a bad sign.

425
00:39:39,755 --> 00:39:42,515
It will be hard to stitch it up
in that condition.

426
00:39:47,844 --> 00:39:48,667
Are you having fun?

427
00:39:48,667 --> 00:39:51,751
I'd start over if it were me.

428
00:39:51,751 --> 00:39:54,341
It's better that way.

429
00:40:15,791 --> 00:40:17,042
Shi Won.

430
00:40:17,957 --> 00:40:20,334
You should've been careful.

431
00:40:20,334 --> 00:40:23,000
How did you hurt your hand?

432
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,630
It's okay.

433
00:40:24,630 --> 00:40:26,167
Aren't you busy?

434
00:40:26,167 --> 00:40:27,709
To prepare
for your study abroad and performance.

435
00:40:27,709 --> 00:40:29,250
Who cares about studying abroad?

436
00:40:29,250 --> 00:40:30,667
Your arm is in this condition.

437
00:40:30,667 --> 00:40:32,209
I'm fine.

438
00:40:32,209 --> 00:40:34,500
Let me see it now!

439
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:38,979
I'm really fine. It doesn't hurt or anything.

440
00:40:46,681 --> 00:40:48,941
Do we now have a special relationship?

441
00:40:51,824 --> 00:40:54,327
As someone
who is in a special relationship with you,

442
00:40:54,327 --> 00:40:56,584
I'll kill you if you cheat on me.

443
00:40:56,584 --> 00:40:58,958
If you look elsewhere, I'll kill you.

444
00:40:59,767 --> 00:41:01,068
Okay.

445
00:41:04,047 --> 00:41:07,309
I'll be right back.

446
00:41:25,152 --> 00:41:28,788
I'm on my way to Il Lak,
take care of your own dinner.

447
00:41:30,199 --> 00:41:32,083
Am I your personal restaurant?

448
00:41:32,083 --> 00:41:34,535
Why are you ordering your dinner
over the phone?

449
00:42:00,768 --> 00:42:05,500
She even wore a necklace for the shooting!

450
00:42:05,500 --> 00:42:09,445
This is an important necklace
that my father gave me as a gift.

451
00:42:10,155 --> 00:42:12,249
You also got your hair done.

452
00:42:12,866 --> 00:42:14,459
It's not even noticeable.

453
00:42:15,575 --> 00:42:19,209
- It looks okay.
- Hey, don't even bother with them.

454
00:42:19,209 --> 00:42:21,417
- We're not the old S anymore.
- Of course not.

455
00:42:21,417 --> 00:42:25,085
We're one step closer to a solo recording.

456
00:42:26,171 --> 00:42:28,306
Hello, everyone!

457
00:42:38,225 --> 00:42:41,236
I guess everyone gets along now?

458
00:42:43,698 --> 00:42:46,834
I'm sure you know well
about the direction of this program.

459
00:42:46,834 --> 00:42:49,942
"Friendship and classical music
in a college orchestra."

460
00:42:49,942 --> 00:42:52,709
- Of course, of course.
- Friendship or destiny?

461
00:42:52,709 --> 00:42:54,292
Now, now.

462
00:42:54,292 --> 00:42:56,292
Thank you for your cooperation.

463
00:42:56,292 --> 00:42:57,709
You're welcome!

464
00:42:57,709 --> 00:42:59,250
- Take the camera first.
- Yes.

465
00:42:59,250 --> 00:43:01,756
- Camera?
- Camera?

466
00:43:02,964 --> 00:43:04,582
What's that?

467
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:06,017
When was that there?

468
00:43:06,628 --> 00:43:08,054
What's that?

469
00:43:11,177 --> 00:43:13,271
It's an observation camera.

470
00:43:14,198 --> 00:43:18,626
We got the school permission
to observe the real life of the students.

471
00:43:18,626 --> 00:43:20,683
Didn't you hear anything?

472
00:43:26,562 --> 00:43:30,709
When did you install it?

473
00:43:30,709 --> 00:43:32,611
Last night.

474
00:43:33,861 --> 00:43:35,918
You really weren't notified?

475
00:43:35,918 --> 00:43:38,117
Last night...

476
00:43:42,829 --> 00:43:44,834
The TV program wants to cancel the shooting.

477
00:43:44,834 --> 00:43:47,292
What happened? You really didn't know?

478
00:43:47,292 --> 00:43:51,125
How could the members be divided
and argue badly enough for them to cancel?

479
00:43:51,125 --> 00:43:52,042
I'm sorry.

480
00:43:52,042 --> 00:43:55,125
The TV program notified you ahead of time.

481
00:43:55,125 --> 00:43:57,042
Yes, I heard about it.

482
00:43:57,042 --> 00:43:58,296
So why?

483
00:43:58,296 --> 00:44:00,681
What's going on here?

484
00:44:28,794 --> 00:44:30,429
Professor.

485
00:44:31,270 --> 00:44:33,531
You are not giving her a lesson today?

486
00:44:37,543 --> 00:44:39,670
Nae Il has no motivation.

487
00:44:39,670 --> 00:44:41,930
She can't be like that over a competition.

488
00:44:43,061 --> 00:44:46,459
She must've poured her everything
into her last performance.

489
00:44:46,459 --> 00:44:48,646
Please just give her some time.

490
00:45:22,097 --> 00:45:23,648
Do you want to play together?

491
00:45:54,630 --> 00:45:56,223
It's no fun, is it?

492
00:45:59,006 --> 00:46:00,977
Don't play when you're not having fun.

493
00:46:02,683 --> 00:46:06,444
When I get sick,
I have to be really sick to recover quickly.

494
00:46:07,142 --> 00:46:08,652
Sunbae.

495
00:46:09,428 --> 00:46:13,649
I didn't know I was such a bad person.

496
00:46:15,651 --> 00:46:17,995
I'm really selfish, aren't I?

497
00:46:19,334 --> 00:46:21,959
Yoo Jin is having such a tough time.

498
00:46:23,500 --> 00:46:25,014
I don't want to hear...

499
00:46:26,299 --> 00:46:27,516
about Yoo Jin.

500
00:46:29,122 --> 00:46:30,632
I'm sorry.

501
00:46:33,250 --> 00:46:35,334
No, go ahead.

502
00:46:35,334 --> 00:46:37,304
What's wrong with Yoo Jin?

503
00:46:38,338 --> 00:46:39,931
Well...

504
00:46:49,083 --> 00:46:50,584
Hello?

505
00:46:51,250 --> 00:46:53,128
Hi, Mini Min Hee.

506
00:46:53,834 --> 00:46:55,514
Why?

507
00:46:59,820 --> 00:47:01,663
What happened?

508
00:47:05,909 --> 00:47:09,678
Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin!

509
00:47:12,249 --> 00:47:13,800
We have a big problem!

510
00:47:15,567 --> 00:47:17,834
Recently, at the founding anniversary concert,

511
00:47:17,834 --> 00:47:19,751
the representative orchestra of Han Eum,
Rising Star,

512
00:47:19,751 --> 00:47:22,334
delivered an angelic performance
that drew much praise.

513
00:47:22,334 --> 00:47:25,000
However, they now face
their TV program being canceled

514
00:47:25,000 --> 00:47:27,209
due to serious internal conflict.

515
00:47:27,209 --> 00:47:29,381
- Internal conflict?
- Internal conflict?

516
00:47:57,917 --> 00:47:59,542
What should we do?

517
00:47:59,542 --> 00:48:03,083
If Yoo Jin gets expelled from school
because of us...

518
00:48:03,083 --> 00:48:04,834
No way!

519
00:48:04,834 --> 00:48:07,876
He's Cha Dong Woo's son
and von Stresemann's pupil.

520
00:48:07,876 --> 00:48:09,709
They wouldn't expel him.

521
00:48:09,709 --> 00:48:11,673
No!

522
00:48:12,584 --> 00:48:15,462
Doesn't it look like
someone was determined to do this?

523
00:48:15,462 --> 00:48:16,834
If you think about it,

524
00:48:16,834 --> 00:48:19,057
a lot of things happened recently
that bothered me.

525
00:48:19,987 --> 00:48:24,083
First, the video clip of Sae Hyun that was on
but we don't know who turned it on.

526
00:48:24,083 --> 00:48:27,584
Yes, it's exactly like it was before.

527
00:48:27,584 --> 00:48:29,001
It's not me.

528
00:48:29,868 --> 00:48:31,752
Did anyone say anything?

529
00:48:33,109 --> 00:48:36,788
Second, the observation camera.

530
00:48:37,369 --> 00:48:39,955
It's also strange
that Yoo Jin forgot about that.

531
00:48:40,668 --> 00:48:43,799
And the news article came out
and the board of directors was summoned.

532
00:48:44,417 --> 00:48:47,877
Then who benefited from this?

533
00:48:51,060 --> 00:48:53,124
Isn't it Sae Hyun University?

534
00:48:53,124 --> 00:48:55,542
They got to be on the TV program.

535
00:48:55,542 --> 00:48:58,918
And they're discussing a recording contract
with Lusa.

536
00:48:58,918 --> 00:49:00,849
Lusa.

537
00:49:02,022 --> 00:49:05,125
Then Sae Hyun's video clip was the beginning.

538
00:49:05,125 --> 00:49:09,876
The screen and the projector couldn't
have been brought in from far.

539
00:49:09,876 --> 00:49:11,584
Then where did they come from?

540
00:49:11,584 --> 00:49:13,138
I'll look into it.

541
00:49:13,954 --> 00:49:15,567
By the way...

542
00:49:16,748 --> 00:49:22,303
Are they targeting our orchestra or Yoo Jin?

543
00:49:29,083 --> 00:49:30,250
[Rental Sign-In Sheet]

544
00:49:30,250 --> 00:49:33,083
Please sign there.

545
00:49:33,083 --> 00:49:35,876
The orchestra is renting a projector often
these days.

546
00:49:35,876 --> 00:49:38,344
Why don't you just use the room
with a projector installed?

547
00:49:39,396 --> 00:49:40,626
One of our members

548
00:49:40,626 --> 00:49:42,000
[Rental Sign-In Sheet]

549
00:49:43,500 --> 00:49:45,869
must have rented one?

550
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:52,626
[Projector]

551
00:49:54,533 --> 00:49:59,626
Did this person really rent one?

552
00:49:59,626 --> 00:50:00,626
Yes.

553
00:50:02,669 --> 00:50:05,972
I've never had this kind of humiliation.
Do you understand?

554
00:50:09,891 --> 00:50:10,792
They're too mean.

555
00:50:10,792 --> 00:50:12,417
My goodness, Almighty Cha.

556
00:50:34,782 --> 00:50:36,870
Hello.

557
00:50:36,876 --> 00:50:38,876
Never mind.

558
00:50:38,876 --> 00:50:43,685
I get to see
Yoo Jin being treated like an idiot.

559
00:50:44,119 --> 00:50:46,546
He used to be treated
almost like a professor.

560
00:50:49,004 --> 00:50:52,292
If Sunbae goes to study abroad,

561
00:50:52,292 --> 00:50:54,959
he wouldn't have
to struggle like that, right?

562
00:50:54,959 --> 00:50:56,760
At least that wouldn't happen to him.

563
00:50:58,629 --> 00:51:00,347
I guess not.

564
00:51:02,186 --> 00:51:05,572
If Sunbae goes to study abroad,
he will fly high.

565
00:51:07,359 --> 00:51:09,661
As long as he can get on a flight...

566
00:51:27,283 --> 00:51:28,626
Yoon Hoo, it's been a while.

567
00:51:28,626 --> 00:51:29,834
Yes, Dean.

568
00:51:29,834 --> 00:51:32,881
Oh, and I just joined Rising Star.

569
00:51:32,881 --> 00:51:34,250
I heard. Congratulations.

570
00:51:34,250 --> 00:51:35,918
But I have to go now.

571
00:51:35,918 --> 00:51:37,751
See you later. I'm sorry.

572
00:51:37,751 --> 00:51:41,764
By any chance,
did you also give your permission?

573
00:51:43,709 --> 00:51:45,336
About Cha Yoo Jin.

574
00:51:45,336 --> 00:51:48,013
Cha Yoo Jin's behavior now.

575
00:51:54,602 --> 00:51:58,000
The TV station notified you ahead of time.

576
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:00,142
Yes, I heard about it.

577
00:52:00,142 --> 00:52:01,292
Then why?

578
00:52:01,292 --> 00:52:05,876
They even notified you
about the observation camera.

579
00:52:05,876 --> 00:52:08,409
Did you forget?

580
00:52:09,134 --> 00:52:11,125
No.

581
00:52:11,125 --> 00:52:15,375
I felt that I didn't need to tell them,
so I didn't.

582
00:52:15,375 --> 00:52:16,125
Yoo Jin!

583
00:52:16,125 --> 00:52:19,003
I wanted to show the members...

584
00:52:19,704 --> 00:52:21,641
what they really

585
00:52:23,284 --> 00:52:25,540
look like now.

586
00:52:36,240 --> 00:52:38,208
Yoo Jin.

587
00:52:46,038 --> 00:52:47,665
Just take it off now.

588
00:52:48,582 --> 00:52:51,547
We don't even know
if we'll have a performance or not.

589
00:52:53,549 --> 00:52:55,601
You knew about it?

590
00:52:57,199 --> 00:53:01,754
When I went to your place,
I heard the violin sound from your room.

591
00:53:03,100 --> 00:53:06,237
You did it to hand over the soloist position
to Shi Won, right?

592
00:53:07,543 --> 00:53:08,969
Yeah.

593
00:53:09,630 --> 00:53:13,600
Shi Won is better than me as a soloist.

594
00:53:14,624 --> 00:53:16,209
I wanted to give her the soloist position
as a gift

595
00:53:16,209 --> 00:53:18,292
before she left.

596
00:53:18,292 --> 00:53:23,776
But Shi Won is really better
for the orchestra.

597
00:53:28,333 --> 00:53:30,218
Yoo Il Lak.

598
00:53:31,569 --> 00:53:37,458
To me, there is no better soloist than you
in the orchestra.

599
00:54:16,737 --> 00:54:19,217
We don't know what's ahead of us.

600
00:54:20,032 --> 00:54:22,542
And what consequences to face.

601
00:54:24,269 --> 00:54:27,751
I want to ask you,

602
00:54:28,599 --> 00:54:32,356
do you really want to work it out?

603
00:54:45,494 --> 00:54:47,337
You make the decision.

604
00:54:48,085 --> 00:54:50,500
How did it go?

605
00:54:50,500 --> 00:54:54,441
I guess we'll follow
the decision of the chairwoman.

606
00:54:54,441 --> 00:54:56,134
It won't be easy.

607
00:54:56,877 --> 00:55:02,083
Then, Sunbae,
how bad could the disciplinary action be?

608
00:55:02,083 --> 00:55:03,917
I don't have any idea.

609
00:55:06,098 --> 00:55:09,359
About hypnotherapy...

610
00:55:11,461 --> 00:55:13,876
What's that out of nowhere?

611
00:55:13,876 --> 00:55:17,751
You said it didn't work
when you were treated by the doctor, right?

612
00:55:17,751 --> 00:55:21,250
I'm too self-conscious
or I don't have enough faith.

613
00:55:21,250 --> 00:55:22,876
Something like that.

614
00:55:22,876 --> 00:55:24,709
Faith?

615
00:55:24,709 --> 00:55:26,459
I would have to trust someone enough
to believe

616
00:55:26,459 --> 00:55:28,834
that they'll catch me when I fall.

617
00:55:28,834 --> 00:55:30,959
For hypnosis to be easy.

618
00:55:30,959 --> 00:55:33,680
I guess I don't have that kind of faith
in the doctor.

619
00:55:34,141 --> 00:55:39,334
That means if you trust someone a lot,
hypnosis will work well?

620
00:55:39,334 --> 00:55:41,042
That's what I heard.

621
00:55:41,042 --> 00:55:43,173
It depends on the person, too.

622
00:55:45,590 --> 00:55:49,477
Sunbae, you must trust me a lot.

623
00:55:50,833 --> 00:55:52,843
I don't trust you.

624
00:55:58,939 --> 00:56:01,169
When I count down to one,

625
00:56:01,169 --> 00:56:04,722
you will be in a deep relaxation state.

626
00:56:06,145 --> 00:56:09,740
Deep, deeper.

627
00:56:16,873 --> 00:56:20,169
We will go to the time of the plane accident.

628
00:56:20,792 --> 00:56:27,292
You are on a plane to Berlin now.

629
00:56:27,292 --> 00:56:29,830
What happened?

630
00:56:32,351 --> 00:56:34,570
Grandpa.

631
00:56:35,918 --> 00:56:43,469
An old man who liked Professor Viera
was sitting there.

632
00:56:54,119 --> 00:57:00,751
Are you also going
to see the Berlin Philharmonic?

633
00:57:00,751 --> 00:57:04,907
Yes, Viera is my mentor.

634
00:57:05,922 --> 00:57:08,500
You have a great professor.

635
00:57:08,500 --> 00:57:14,365
Sebastian Viera is a great conductor.

636
00:57:15,432 --> 00:57:21,834
This grandpa goes everywhere
that Teacher Viera conducts.

637
00:57:21,834 --> 00:57:24,042
He's not even that healthy.

638
00:57:24,042 --> 00:57:29,432
Who said she wanted to go
because it's great every time?

639
00:57:45,507 --> 00:57:47,475
Honey!

640
00:57:49,042 --> 00:57:50,417
Hey!

641
00:57:50,417 --> 00:57:52,786
Give me my medicine.

642
00:57:53,599 --> 00:57:56,482
Oh my. It's okay, it's okay.

643
00:58:00,814 --> 00:58:05,535
What are you doing now?

644
00:58:07,186 --> 00:58:08,779
The medicine bottle.

645
00:58:12,367 --> 00:58:15,461
I'm trying to catch the medicine bottle.

646
00:58:17,869 --> 00:58:20,083
Honey! Honey!

647
00:58:20,083 --> 00:58:23,478
Honey! Honey! Wake up!

648
00:58:23,478 --> 00:58:25,613
Flight attendant!

649
00:58:30,052 --> 00:58:32,479
But I couldn't grab it.

650
00:58:34,265 --> 00:58:36,609
I grabbed it.

651
00:58:37,806 --> 00:58:40,626
- Honey! Honey!
- Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin!

652
00:58:40,626 --> 00:58:44,519
Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin!

653
00:58:54,072 --> 00:58:56,500
It's okay.

654
00:58:56,500 --> 00:59:01,273
You did your best to save the grandpa.

655
00:59:04,294 --> 00:59:06,846
I couldn't help.

656
00:59:10,376 --> 00:59:11,769
You're right.

657
00:59:12,678 --> 00:59:15,182
It's not your fault.

658
00:59:20,284 --> 00:59:27,591
You don't need
to feel guilty or afraid anymore.

659
00:59:40,076 --> 00:59:42,198
In a little bit

660
00:59:43,371 --> 00:59:45,836
when the alarm goes off,

661
00:59:46,654 --> 00:59:48,873
open your eyes.

662
00:59:52,075 --> 00:59:54,460
When you open your eyes,

663
00:59:55,570 --> 00:59:57,580
you...

664
01:00:05,480 --> 01:00:07,323
Now you...

665
01:00:14,275 --> 01:00:15,868
Now...

666
01:00:20,052 --> 01:00:21,854
when you open your eyes,

667
01:00:22,597 --> 01:00:24,732
you can...

668
01:00:26,502 --> 01:00:29,388
get on a plane.

669
01:00:35,067 --> 01:00:37,369
You can get on a plane...

670
01:00:38,191 --> 01:00:43,288
and you can go anywhere.
